  "What is 'logarithmic differentiation'?": "什么是“对数差异”?",
  "Using the log rule for integration": "使用日日志规则集成",
  "Differentiating logarithmic functions directly": "直接区分对对数函数",
  "Converting all functions to exponentials": "将全部函数转换成指数",
  "A technique where you take the natural log of both sides of y = f(x), then differentiate": "一种技术,其中您使用 y = f(x) 的两侧的自然日志,然后区分",
  "Logarithmic differentiation involves: (1) taking ln of both sides: ln(y) = ln(f(x)), (2) using log properties to simplify, (3) differentiating both sides, and (4) solving for y'. It is especially useful for functions of the form f(x)^g(x).": "对数区分涉及:(1) 在两边使用: In(y) = In(f(x)),(2) 使用日志属性简化,(3) 区分两边,(4) 解决y'。 它对于表f(x) g(x) 的功能特别有用。",
  "When is logarithmic differentiation most useful?": "对数区分何时最有用?",
  "For simple polynomial functions": "对于简单的多元函数",
  "For integration problems": "关于融合问题",
  "Only for constant exponents": "仅用于常列指数",
  "For products, quotients, and powers where f(x)^g(x) appears": "对于产品、商数和显示 f(x)xg(x) 的功率",
  "Logarithmic differentiation is most useful for: (1) functions raised to variable powers like x^x, (2) complicated products/quotients that simplify with log properties, and (3) any expression where standard rules are cumbersome.": "对数区分对以下各点最为有用:(1) 向诸如xxx等变数权力提出功能,(2) 使用对数属性简化的复杂产品/引用,(3) 标准规则繁琐的任何表达方式。",
  "What does 'ln(y)' represent in logarithmic differentiation?": "对数差异中“ ln(y)” 代表什么 ?",
  "The derivative of y under most circumstances involving differentiation": "y的衍生物在多数情况下涉及差异化",
  "The integral of y in most scenarios involving differentiation factors": "在涉及差异因素的大多数假设情况中,y的内在组成部分",
  "The reciprocal of y, despite what intuition might initially suggest": "y的对等 尽管直觉最初可能暗示",
  "The natural logarithm of the function y, used to simplify the expression before differentiating": "函数 Y 的自然对数,用于在区分前简化表达式",
  "Taking ln(y) converts products to sums, quotients to differences, and exponents to coefficients via log properties. This makes the subsequent differentiation much simpler.": "“接受(y) ” 将产品转换成数量,将商数转换成差异,并通过日志属性将指数转换成系数。 这使得随后的差别化简单得多。",
  "What does the equation (1/y) * y' = ... represent in logarithmic differentiation?": "等式 (1/y) * y' =... 在对数差异中代表什么?",
  "The product rule applied to 1/y": "适用于 1/y 的 产品规则",
  "The inverse function theorem": "反反函数定理",
  "The result of differentiating ln(y) using the chain rule: d/dx[ln(y)] = y'/y": "使用链规则区分 In(y) 的结果: d/dx[ln(y)] = y'/y",
  "The quotient rule applied to y": "y 所适用的商数规则",
  "When we differentiate ln(y) with respect to x, the chain rule gives d/dx[ln(y)] = (1/y) * dy/dx = y'/y. This is the key step in logarithmic differentiation.": "当我们对 x 进行 In(y) 区分时, 链规则给出 d/ dx[ ln(y)] = (1/ y) * dy/ dx = y' /y。 这是对数区分的关键步骤 。",
  "What logarithmic property converts products into sums?": "哪些对数属性将产品转换成总数?",
  "ln(a/b) = ln(a) + ln(b)": "In(a/b) = In(a) + In(b) = In(a) + In(b)",
  "ln(a * b) = ln(a) * ln(b)": "In(a) * (b) = In(a) * In(b)",
  "ln(a * b) = ln(a) + ln(b)": "In(a) * b) = In(a) + In(b)",
  "ln(a + b) = ln(a) * ln(b)": "In(a) +(b) = In(a) = In(b)",
  "The product rule for logarithms states ln(ab) = ln(a) + ln(b). This is why logarithmic differentiation simplifies products: taking ln turns them into sums, which are easier to differentiate.": "对数产品规则表示 In(a) = In(a) + In(b) 。 这就是为什么对数区别简化产品的原因:将它们变为总和,这更容易区分。",
  "What logarithmic property converts quotients into differences?": "哪些对数属性将商数转换为差异?",
  "ln(a/b) = ln(a) - ln(b)": "In(a/b) = In(a) - In(b)",
  "ln(a/b) = ln(a) / ln(b)": "In(a/b) = In(a) / in(b)",
  "ln(a - b) = ln(a)/ln(b)": "In(a-b) = In(a)/ln(b)",
  "The quotient rule for logarithms states ln(a/b) = ln(a) - ln(b). This converts division into subtraction, making quotients easier to differentiate after taking the natural log.": "对数的商数规则表示 In(a/b) = In(a) - In(b) 。 这会将除法转换为减法, 使使用自然对数后更容易区分商数 。",
  "What logarithmic property converts powers into coefficients?": "何为对数属性将功率转换为系数?",
  "ln(a^n) = ln(a)^n": "In(a)n = In(a)n",
  "ln(a^n) = n + ln(a)": "In(an) = n + In(a)",
