  "ln(a^n) = n * ln(a)": "In(a)n = n * In(a)",
  "The power rule for logarithms states ln(a^n) = n*ln(a). The exponent becomes a multiplier. When n is a function of x (like in x^x), this is essential for logarithmic differentiation.": "对数规则表示 In( an) = n*ln(a) 。 引号变为乘数。 当 n 是 x 的函数时( 类似 xx) , 这对于对数区分至关重要 。",
  "Why can't the power rule d/dx[x^n] = nx^(n-1) be used for x^x?": "为何不能将权力规则 d/dx[xn] = nx(n-1) 用于 xx ?",
  "Because the chain rule applies instead according to widely held views on this topic": "因为根据对本专题广泛持有的意见,链规则反而适用",
  "Because the power rule requires a constant exponent, and in x^x both the base and exponent depend on x": "因为权力规则需要一个恒定的指数, 在 xxx 中, 基础和指数都依赖于 x",
  "Because x must be positive, at least according to standard theory": "因为x必须是积极的, 至少根据标准理论",
  "Because x^x is undefined, which is a common assumption in the field": "因为 xx 是未定义的, 这是字段中常见的假设",
  "The power rule applies when the exponent is constant. In x^x, the exponent x varies, so neither the power rule nor the exponential rule d/dx[a^x] = a^x*ln(a) applies directly. Logarithmic differentiation handles this case.": "当指数不变时适用权力规则。在 xxx 中,指数值 x 不同,因此权力规则或指数规则 d/dx[ax] = ax*ln(a) 都不适用。对数差异处理此例。",
